<!DOCTYPE task PUBLIC "-//OASIS//DTD DITA Task//EN" "task.dtd">
<task id="task_gbx_4l3_zcb">
    <title>NCSU Moodle - Checking Grades</title>
    <shortdesc>How to Check Course Grades Through Moodle
</shortdesc>
    <prolog><metadata><prodinfo>
        <prodname>Moodle </prodname>
    </prodinfo></metadata></prolog>
    <taskbody>
        <context>Checking your grades through Moodle is a super simple process. The first step is getting to the Moodle dashboard itself. Let’s get started!
</context>
        <steps>
            <step>
                <cmd>Step 1) Log into WolfWare 
</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Log into your WolfWare account at https://wolfware.ncsu.edu/ using your Unity ID and password. </cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Once you have logged into your WolfWare account, select the Moodle Symbol next to the course that you want to check your grades in. 
</cmd>
               
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Step 2) Find and Select the “Grades” Tab</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Once you have arrived at your chosen course’s Moodle page, you will see a small, gray symbol in the upper left hand corner </cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Once you select the small gray symbol in the upper left corner, an index for that course’s Moodle page will appear  
</cmd>
               
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Within the index, select the tab labeled “Grades”. There you will find all the listed grades for your course. 
</cmd>
           
        </steps>
    </taskbody>
</task>
